@achilles  
Some proto-equipment uses the falls away method, some doesn't (like [Tawnos's Weaponry](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Tawnos's Weaponry)). I think the earliest use was [Sandals of Abdallah](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Sandals of Abdallah), and in flavor terms it makes a lot of sense for them to disappear: they let you walk on water, and if you die while doing so, you and they both sink. Similarly, [Flying Carpet](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Flying Carpet) was lost in the user's fatal plummet, until Classic Sixth Edition when they tried to fix the card by removing that stipulation. (Sixth is the only set I know of to deliberately change card text to make cards better than originally intended.)  

@Ava  
